rComments: He either likes you or he doesn't, and that will predetermine your grade. He will give you positive feedback and/or a positive critique and strap you with a terrible mark. Condescending and fake.

Nice guy, excellent teacher. As with most art profs, whether you like him comes down to whether you agree with his personal tastes. I like him because his opinions happen to be correct. He's also seems to be more in touch with the local art scene, probably because he's younger than a lot of UT vis profs.
very conceptual.  slightly narrow minded but as are all artists in their own time period.  reasonable marker, good lectuer. HORRIBLE FRENCH pronounciation... the irony is that his name is jean paul.
good luck. he takes so long to mark and is very hard to get a hold of. gives mixed messages when you ask for feedback or ideas
